# .skills — Reusable Patterns & Recipes for AI Coding Assistants

This file documents established patterns used in this project.
When asked to add a feature, always follow the patterns below.

---

## 1. Add a New Backend Resource (Full CRUD)

Follow the layered pattern: **Route → Controller → Service → Prisma**

### Step 1 — Add model to `prisma/schema.prisma`
```prisma
model Post {
  id        Int     @id @default(autoincrement())
  title     String
  content   String? @db.Text
  authorId  Int
  author    Usuario @relation(fields: [authorId], references: [id])
}
```
Then run:
```bash
npx prisma migrate dev --name add_post
npx prisma generate
```

### Step 2 — Create `src/services/postService.ts`
```typescript
import { prisma } from "../config/database.js";

export const postService = {
  async getAll() {
    return prisma.post.findMany();
  },
  async getById(id: number) {
    return prisma.post.findUnique({ where: { id } });
  },
  async create(data: { title: string; content?: string; authorId: number }) {
    return prisma.post.create({ data });
  },
  async updateById(id: number, data: Partial<{ title: string; content: string }>) {
    return prisma.post.update({ where: { id }, data });
  },
  async deleteById(id: number) {
    return prisma.post.delete({ where: { id } });
  },
};
```

### Step 3 — Create `src/controllers/postController.ts`
```typescript
import { Request, Response } from "express";
import { postService } from "../services/postService.js";

export const postController = {
  async getAll(req: Request, res: Response) {
    const posts = await postService.getAll();
    res.json(posts);
  },
  async getById(req: Request, res: Response) {
    const post = await postService.getById(Number(req.params.id));
    if (!post) return res.status(404).json({ error: "Not found" });
    res.json(post);
  },
  async create(req: Request, res: Response) {
    const post = await postService.create(req.body);
    res.status(201).json(post);
  },
  async update(req: Request, res: Response) {
    const post = await postService.updateById(Number(req.params.id), req.body);
    res.json(post);
  },
  async remove(req: Request, res: Response) {
    await postService.deleteById(Number(req.params.id));
    res.status(204).send();
  },
};
```

### Step 4 — Create `src/routes/postRoute.ts`
```typescript
import { Router } from "express";
import { postController } from "../controllers/postController.js";

const router = Router();

router.get("/", postController.getAll);
router.get("/:id", postController.getById);
router.post("/", postController.create);
router.put("/:id", postController.update);
router.delete("/:id", postController.remove);

export default router;
```

### Step 5 — Register route in `server.ts`
```typescript
import postRouter from "./src/routes/postRoute.ts";
app.use(express.json());
app.use("/posts", postRouter);
```

---

## 2. Add a New Frontend Page

### Step 1 — Create component in `frontend/src/components/`
```tsx
// frontend/src/components/Posts.tsx
export function Posts() {
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>Posts</h1>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Step 2 — Register route in `frontend/src/routes.tsx`
```tsx
import { Posts } from './components/Posts';

// Inside <Routes>:
<Route path="/posts" element={<Posts />} />
```

---

## 3. Fetch Data from Backend in a React Component

```tsx
import { useEffect, useState } from "react";

type Post = { id: number; title: string; content?: string };

export function Posts() {
  const [posts, setPosts] = useState<Post[]>([]);
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);

  useEffect(() => {
    fetch("/api/posts")
      .then((r) => r.json())
      .then((data) => {
        setPosts(data);
        setLoading(false);
      });
  }, []);

  if (loading) return <p>Loading...</p>;

  return (
    <ul>
      {posts.map((p) => (
        <li key={p.id}>{p.title}</li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  );
}
```

> Configure Vite dev proxy in `frontend/vite.config.ts` to forward `/api` to `http://localhost:PORT`.

---

## 4. Vite Dev Proxy Setup (avoid CORS in development)

```typescript
// frontend/vite.config.ts
import { defineConfig } from 'vite';
import react from '@vitejs/plugin-react';

export default defineConfig({
  plugins: [react()],
  server: {
    proxy: {
      '/api': {
        target: 'http://localhost:3000',
        changeOrigin: true,
        rewrite: (path) => path.replace(/^\/api/, ''),
      },
    },
  },
});
```

---

## 5. Add Environment Variable (Backend)

1. Add to `backend/.env`:
   ```
   MY_SECRET=value
   ```
2. Add to `backend/.env.example` (no real value):
   ```
   MY_SECRET=
   ```
3. Access in code:
   ```typescript
   const secret = process.env.MY_SECRET;
   ```
> `dotenv/config` is already imported in `server.ts` — no extra setup needed.

---

## 6. Prisma Client Singleton Pattern

Already set up in `backend/src/config/database.ts`. Always import from there:
```typescript
import { prisma } from "../config/database.js";
```
Never instantiate `new PrismaClient()` outside that file.

---

## 7. Error Handling Pattern (Backend)

Wrap controller methods in try/catch or use an error-handling middleware:

```typescript
// Global error handler — register last in server.ts
app.use((err: Error, req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {
  console.error(err.stack);
  res.status(500).json({ error: err.message });
});
```

For async controllers, use:
```typescript
export const getAll = async (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {
  try {
    const data = await myService.getAll();
    res.json(data);
  } catch (error) {
    next(error);
  }
};
```

---

## 8. Docker — Start / Stop Database

```bash
# Start Postgres container
cd backend && docker-compose up -d

# Stop without removing data
docker-compose stop

# Stop and remove volumes (wipe DB)
docker-compose down -v
```

---

## 9. Adding a TailwindCSS v4 Utility Class

TailwindCSS v4 scans your files automatically (no `content` config needed).
Just add classes directly in JSX:
```tsx
<div className="flex items-center gap-4 p-6 bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-md">
  ...
</div>
```

---

## 10. TypeScript Import Convention (Backend)

Because the backend uses `"type": "module"` (ESM), always use `.js` extensions in imports even for `.ts` source files:
```typescript
// ✅ Correct
import { userService } from "../services/userService.js";

// ❌ Wrong
import { userService } from "../services/userService";
```

---

## Quick Reference — Common Prisma Queries

```typescript
// Find all
await prisma.usuario.findMany();

// Find one by id
await prisma.usuario.findUnique({ where: { id } });

// Create
await prisma.usuario.create({ data: { name, email } });

// Update
await prisma.usuario.update({ where: { id }, data: { name } });

// Delete
await prisma.usuario.delete({ where: { id } });

// Find with relation
await prisma.usuario.findMany({ include: { coments: true } });

// Upsert
await prisma.usuario.upsert({
  where: { email },
  update: { name },
  create: { name, email },
});
```
